+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LFSB> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Conglomerate, sandstone and siltstone with subsidiary non-carbonate salt-rock. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Courceyan Substage - to - Chadian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (359.3-344.5 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LMBA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mudstone with subsidiary sandstone and tuffaceous-siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Selandian Age - to - Thanetian Age (Palaeogene Period) (61.7-56 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LMBT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mudstone with subsidiary sandstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Thanetian Age - to - Ypresian Age (Palaeogene Period) (59.2-48.1 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/LMS> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Sandstone with subsidiary breccia, conglomerate and mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Cisuralian Epoch - to - Lopingian Epoch (Permian Period) (298.9-251.9 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MAVO> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Basaltic-trachyandesite lava, sandstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Cisuralian Epoch (Permian Period) (298.9-274.4 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MKFG> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Ganister. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Pendleian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (330.3-327 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MOSSA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Sandstone with subsidiary lignite, mudstone, sandy limestone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Miocene Epoch (Neogene Period) (23.04-5.33 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/MYGL> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Brigantian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (330.9-330.3 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NEPT> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Sandstone with subsidiary mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Hauterivian Age - to - Aptian Age (Cretaceous Period) (132.6-113.2 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NORDL> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Sandstone with subsidiary mudstone and trace lignite. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Miocene Epoch (Neogene Period) (23.04-5.33 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NORDM> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mud and sand. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Pliocene Epoch (Neogene Period) - to - Mid Pleistocene (Quaternary Period) (5.33-.126 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NORDU> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Diamicton. Stratified superficial deposits. Occurs offshore. Formed during the Mid Pleistocene - to - Holocene Epoch (Quaternary Period) (.78-0 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/NUNV> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Basaltic-trachyandesite lava. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Cisuralian Epoch (Permian Period) (298.9-274.4 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/OCKS> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Limestone and sandstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Danian Age (Palaeogene Period) (66-61.7 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/OG> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Obsolete name. Limestone, mudstone and sandstone with subsidiary siltstone and trace coal. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Chadian Substage - to - Holkerian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (346.7-337 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/OTBA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Mudstone, sandstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Early Triassic Epoch (Triassic Period) (251.9-246.7 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/PLDO> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Dolomite-mudstone and dolostone with subsidiary anhydrite-stone and limestone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Guadalupian Epoch - to - Lopingian Epoch (Permian Period) (274.4-251.9 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RGL> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Limestone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs onshore. Deposited during the Arnsbergian Substage (Carboniferous Period) (327-323.75 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RIDCO> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Conglomerate. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Kimmeridgian Age (Jurassic Period) - to - Berriasian Age (Cretaceous Period) (154.8-137.7 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/RONA> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Conglomerate, mudstone, sandstone and siltstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Bajocian Age - to - Tithonian Age (Jurassic Period) (170.9-143.1 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ROSO> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Conglomerate and sandstone with subsidiary mudstone. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Aptian Age - to - Albian Age (Cretaceous Period) (121.4-100.5 Ma BP)."@en .
+<http://data.bgs.ac.uk/id/Lexicon/NamedRockUnit/ROWF> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "Limestone with subsidiary chert. Stratified bedrock. Occurs offshore. Deposited during the Campanian Age - to - Maastrichtian Age (Cretaceous Period) (83.7-66 Ma BP)."@en .
